The paper discusses the development and analysis of low-complexity iterative thresholding algorithms for reconstructing sparse signals from linear measurements, which is a problem in compressed sensing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the empirical evidence and numerical simulations, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
